one day or another,
I would have probably done it myself.

246
00:34:12,676 --> 00:34:15,554
- Your mother, she...
- She's not my mother.

247
00:34:16,138 --> 00:34:21,143
My sister, she wanted to lose some weight
anyway. Bet she never looked better.

248
00:34:21,602 --> 00:34:24,647
She's not even my real sister.
Just a half sister.

249
00:34:24,730 --> 00:34:26,690
Not a good half at that.

250
00:34:37,326 --> 00:34:39,036
If you couldn't stand them,
why are you crying?

251
00:34:39,119 --> 00:34:41,413
Because they killed my brother.

252
00:34:42,456 --> 00:34:45,709
What the hell did he do?
He was four years old.

253
00:34:46,669 --> 00:34:48,587
He never used to cry.

254
00:34:48,671 --> 00:34:51,548
He just used to sit next to me and cuddle.

255
00:34:53,842 --> 00:34:57,763
I was more of a mother to him
than that goddamned pig ever was.

256
00:34:57,846 --> 00:35:02,351
Hey, don't talk like that about pigs.
They're usually much nicer than people.

257
00:35:02,434 --> 00:35:04,478
But they smell like shit.

258
00:35:06,438 --> 00:35:07,856
Not true.

259
00:35:07,940 --> 00:35:12,778
As a matter of fact,
right now I have one in my kitchen,

260
00:35:12,861 --> 00:35:14,780
that's very clean,

261
00:35:14,863 --> 00:35:18,659
- and smells very nice.
- You don't have a pig in your kitchen.

262
00:35:21,245 --> 00:35:22,287
Yes, I do.

263
00:35:22,371 --> 00:35:25,541
I was just in there,
and I didn't see any goddamn pig.

264
00:35:26,208 --> 00:35:28,252
Don't move. I'll get him.

265
00:35:31,046 --> 00:35:33,215
Piggy, Piggy, where are you?

266
00:35:34,508 --> 00:35:36,010
There you are.

267
00:35:43,392 --> 00:35:45,561
Hi, Mathilda.

268
00:35:46,729 --> 00:35:48,063
Hi, Piggy.

269
00:35:57,114 --> 00:35:59,074
How are you today?

270
00:36:00,242 --> 00:36:02,119
I've seen better days.

271
00:36:09,918 --> 00:36:13,797
- What's your name?
- Leon.

272
00:36:17,551 --> 00:36:18,927
Cute name.

273
00:36:25,309 --> 00:36:28,896
You have anyone to go to,
any family anyplace else?

274
00:36:41,366 --> 00:36:43,577
I'm gonna get some more milk.

275
00:37:01,970 --> 00:37:03,472
Holy shit.

276
00:37:09,812 --> 00:37:11,814
Don't touch that, please.

277
00:37:12,481 --> 00:37:15,400
Leon, what exactly do you do for a living?

278
00:37:17,069 --> 00:37:18,320
Cleaner.

279
00:37:19,988 --> 00:37:23,325
- You mean you're a hit man?
- Yeah.

280
00:37:25,702 --> 00:37:26,829
Cool.

281
00:37:39,633 --> 00:37:43,512
- Do you clean anyone?
- No women, no kids. That's the rules.

282
00:37:44,096 --> 00:37:47,141
How much would it cost to hire someone
to get those dirt bags

283
00:37:47,224 --> 00:37:49,101
who killed my brother?

284
00:37:50,269 --> 00:37:52,521
- Five grand a head.
- Wow.

285
00:37:54,648 --> 00:37:57,651
How about this? I work for you,

286
00:37:58,193 --> 00:38:01,363
and in exchange,
you teach me how to clean?

287
00:38:03,448 --> 00:38:04,741
What do you think?

288
00:38:04,825 --> 00:38:06,994
I'll clean your place. I'll do the shopping.

289
00:38:07,077 --> 00:38:09,204
I'll even wash your clothes.

290
00:38:10,539 --> 00:38:14,459
- Is it a deal?
- No, it's not a deal.

291
00:38:22,342 --> 00:38:26,847
What do you want me to do?
I've got no place to go.

292
00:38:28,265 --> 00:38:30,893
You've had a rough day today.

293
00:38:34,188 --> 00:38:37,149
Go to sleep, and we'll see tomorrow. Okay?

294
00:38:51,455 --> 00:38:54,166
You've been really great with me, Leon,

295
00:38:54,249 --> 00:38:56,501
and it's not always like that.

296
00:38:57,419 --> 00:38:58,712
You know?

297
00:39:07,262 --> 00:39:08,639
Good night.

298
00:40:26,133 --> 00:40:28,844
Sleep well? Good.

299
00:40:28,927 --> 00:40:30,846
Because after breakfast you got to take off.

300
00:40:30,929 --> 00:40:32,931
- Where to?
- Not my problem.

301
00:40:49,531 --> 00:40:51,033
Read it.

302
00:40:57,706 --> 00:40:59,583
You don't know how to read.

303
00:40:59,666 --> 00:41:02,586
I'm learning, but I've had a lot of work lately,

304
00:41:02,669 --> 00:41:05,422
so I'm a little behind.

305
00:41:05,797 --> 00:41:07,257
What's it say?

306
00:41:07,341 --> 00:41:11,136
I've decided what to do with my life.
I want to be a cleaner.

307
00:41:11,887 --> 00:41:16,433
You want to be a cleaner. Here. Take it.

308
00:41:16,892 --> 00:41:20,771
It's a goodbye gift.
Go clean, but not with me.

309
00:41:20,854 --> 00:41:24,316
- I work alone. Understand? Alone.
- Bonnie and Clyde didn't work alone.

310
00:41:24,399 --> 00:41:28,153
Thelma and Louise didn't work alone.
And they were the best.

311
00:41:29,446 --> 00:41:32,866
Mathilda, why are you doing this to me?

312
00:41:33,825 --> 00:41:35,827
I've been nothing but nice to you.

313
00:41:35,911 --> 00:41:39,331
I even saved your life yesterday,
right outside the door.

314
00:41:39,414 --> 00:41:42,167
Right. So now you're responsible for it.

315
00:41:42,751 --> 00:41:46,171
If you saved my life,
you must've saved it for a good reason.

316
00:41:46,254 --> 00:41:49,007
If you throw me out now,
it's like you never opened your door,

317
00:41:49,091 --> 00:41:52,177
like you let me die right there in front of it.

318
00:41:52,260 --> 00:41:55,931
But you did open it. So...

319
00:41:58,558 --> 00:41:59,851
Mathilda...

320
00:42:00,394 --> 00:42:04,106
If you don't help me, I'll die tonight.
I can feel it.

321
00:42:05,023 --> 00:42:07,484
Now, I don't want to die tonight.

322
00:42:08,610 --> 00:42:11,530
Mathilda, you're just a little girl.

323
00:42:11,613 --> 00:42:15,242
So don't take it badly,
but I don't think you could do it.

324
00:42:15,325 --> 00:42:16,660
I'm sorry.

325
00:42:35,720 --> 00:42:37,097
How's that?

326
00:43:08,336 --> 00:43:09,588
Mathilda.

327
00:43:11,381 --> 00:43:14,468
Don't you ever do that again
or I'll break your head.

328
00:43:14,551 --> 00:43:17,137
- You got that?
- Okay.

329
00:43:17,220 --> 00:43:20,307
I don't work like that. It's not professional.

330
00:43:20,599 --> 00:43:23,393
- There is rules.
- Okay.

331
00:43:23,810 --> 00:43:26,563
And stop saying "okay" all the time, okay?

332
00:43:27,772 --> 00:43:28,982
Okay.

333
00:43:29,691 --> 00:43:30,775
Good.

334
00:43:43,914 --> 00:43:44,956
Hi.

335
00:43:46,791 --> 00:43:49,377
You expect to use that in this hotel?

336
00:43:50,879 --> 00:43:53,590
Mister, I have to use it,

337
00:43:53,924 --> 00:43:57,719
because I have an audition
at Juilliard next month

338
00:43:58,261 --> 00:44:00,180
and I have to practice.

339
00:44:00,889 --> 00:44:03,808
Okay, okay, okay, but not after 10:00.

340
00:44:04,142 --> 00:44:06,728
- Okay, I promise.
- All right.

341
00:44:07,812 --> 00:44:10,774
I'll put you at the end of the hall,

342
00:44:11,566 --> 00:44:13,985
so that you don't disturb anyone.

343
00:44:14,861 --> 00:44:17,322
And would you fill those out, please?

344
00:44:21,284 --> 00:44:26,122
Daddy, can I please fill them out?
You know how I like to check in to hotels.

345
00:44:29,918 --> 00:44:32,462
Thanks, Pop.
I'll bring these back in a minute.

346
00:44:32,546 --> 00:44:35,423
- Fourth floor!
- Thanks, mister!

347
00:44:36,258 --> 00:44:40,220
You're lucky to have a little girl
that's interested in things.

348
00:44:41,596 --> 00:44:44,766
I have a kid, 17, does nothing all day long.

349
00:44:50,689 --> 00:44:54,276
Can I leave my plant here
while I take my stuff upstairs?

350
00:44:54,442 --> 00:44:55,777
Of course.

351
00:45:02,117 --> 00:45:03,159
Hi.

352
00:45:16,131 --> 00:45:19,968
I'm putting in a name of a girl
in my class who makes me sick.

353
00:45:22,512 --> 00:45:25,265
If things get hot, she'll take the heat.

354
00:45:43,783 --> 00:45:46,995
- There. Finished.
- How old are you?

355
00:45:47,621 --> 00:45:50,624
- 18.
- 18?

356
00:45:51,708 --> 00:45:54,377
- Want to see my license?
- No.

357
00:45:55,337 --> 00:45:59,507
- Just look a little younger.
- Thanks.

358
00:46:07,849 --> 00:46:11,019
Leon, I want you to teach me
how to be like you.

359
00:46:11,853 --> 00:46:15,190
- I want to be strong like you, smart like you.
- Mathilda.

360
00:46:15,273 --> 00:46:17,692
I know I'm not strong enough yet,

361
00:46:18,526 --> 00:46:21,696
but I could learn the basics, the theory.

362
00:46:22,614 --> 00:46:25,450
What do you think? Just the theory.

363
00:46:27,410 --> 00:46:29,079
I need this, Leon.

364
00:46:30,789 --> 00:46:32,791
I need time to get my head together.

365
00:46:32,874 --> 00:46:34,459
Yeah, and I need

366
00:46:41,966 --> 00:46:43,134
a drink.

367
00:46:44,135 --> 00:46:46,262
Don't move. I'll go get one.

368
00:47:11,246 --> 00:47:14,666
You know, when you told me
to get this baby out for you,

369
00:47:14,749 --> 00:47:16,918
I thought my hearing's going.

370
00:47:17,085 --> 00:47:21,506
I says to myself, "Leon's a pro.
Nobody uses that except beginners."

371
00:47:22,132 --> 00:47:23,842
I like to stay in shape.

372
00:47:23,925 --> 00:47:27,387
Sure. Always stay on top.

373
00:47:28,471 --> 00:47:31,474
It's like me. I got to know
where everything is all the time.

374
00:47:31,558 --> 00:47:35,812
That's why I never leave this place,
except to go from here to there.

375
00:47:38,356 --> 00:47:40,984
Change ain't good, Leon. You know?

376
00:47:45,113 --> 00:47:46,239
Yeah.

377
00:47:52,078 --> 00:47:53,329
Check it.

378
00:47:55,331 --> 00:47:57,625
- Make sure it's the right thing.
- I trust you.

379
00:47:57,709 --> 00:48:01,796
One thing's got nothing to do with the other.
Remember that, Leon.

380
00:48:02,464 --> 00:48:03,673
I will.

381
00:48:19,105 --> 00:48:22,150
The rifle is the first weapon
you learn how to use,

382
00:48:22,233 --> 00:48:25,695
because it lets you
keep your distance from the client.

383
00:48:26,029 --> 00:48:28,198
The closer you get to being a pro,

384
00:48:28,281 --> 00:48:30,867
the closer you can get to the client.

385
00:48:31,659 --> 00:48:34,996
The knife, for example,
is the last thing you learn.

386
00:48:36,623 --> 00:48:39,125
- Okay?
- Okay.

387
00:48:40,960 --> 00:48:42,212
Position.

388
00:49:04,108 --> 00:49:05,193
No.

389
00:49:06,402 --> 00:49:10,114
Never take it off until the last minute.
It reflects light.

390
00:49:10,532 --> 00:49:13,368
They can see you coming from a mile away.

391
00:49:13,451 --> 00:49:16,496
And always dress down.

392
00:49:17,080 --> 00:49:21,084
- Never brighter than the floor, okay?
- Okay.

393
00:49:23,670 --> 00:49:26,756
Let's practice now. It's the best way to learn.

394
00:49:27,882 --> 00:49:30,969
- Who should I hit?
- Whoever.

395
00:49:38,560 --> 00:49:40,061
I'll be with you in a second.
Give me a few minutes.

396
00:49:40,144 --> 00:49:41,688
Thank you. Thanks a lot.
You guys in the suits get lost.

397
00:49:41,771 --> 00:49:43,523
I don't want to see you, all right?

398
00:49:43,606 --> 00:49:46,901
- <i>Is everyone in position?</i>
- This has to look natural.

399
00:49:56,619 --> 00:49:59,205
- No women, no kids, right?
- Right.

400
00:50:07,589 --> 00:50:10,258
- Jogger in the yellow and orange?
- Okay.

401
00:50:14,345 --> 00:50:15,722
Keep calm.

402
00:50:20,101 --> 00:50:22,270
Don't take your eyes off him.

403
00:50:23,938 --> 00:50:25,440
Breathe easy.

404
00:50:27,442 --> 00:50:29,152
Watch his movement.

405
00:50:31,362 --> 00:50:33,781
Pretend you're running with him.

406
00:50:37,702 --> 00:50:39,954
Try to feel his next movement.

407
00:50:41,706 --> 00:50:43,833
Take a deep breath. Hold it.

408
00:50:53,635 --> 00:50:56,512
- Now.
- Oh, my God!

409
00:50:56,721 --> 00:50:58,598
- Get down!
- I'm all right. I'm fine. I'm fine.

410
00:50:58,681 --> 00:51:00,892
Get down! Get down!
Where'd that come from?

411
00:51:00,975 --> 00:51:02,852
One shot. Not bad, huh?

412
00:51:04,228 --> 00:51:06,564
What the hell? I'm fine.
I just can't breathe! Get off of me.

413
00:51:06,648 --> 00:51:09,651
- Stay down!
- Can we try with real bullets now?

414
00:51:10,818 --> 00:51:12,820
Not today. Let's pack up.

415
00:51:21,663 --> 00:51:22,997
They go like that.

416
00:51:24,248 --> 00:51:26,292
Here. After...

417
00:52:06,708 --> 00:52:08,876
- No, thanks.
- No discussion.

418
00:52:50,918 --> 00:52:52,295
"It seemed

419
00:52:54,255 --> 00:52:55,882
"to Socrates..."

420
00:52:58,843 --> 00:53:01,429
"To Socrates..."

421
00:53:04,015 --> 00:53:05,391
I'll do it.

422
00:53:19,947 --> 00:53:21,949
Leon, all we do is work.

423
00:53:22,617 --> 00:53:25,453
We need a break. Let's play a game.

424
00:53:26,370 --> 00:53:29,373
- What kind of game?
- I have this great game.

425
00:53:29,457 --> 00:53:33,711
It makes you think and it helps your memory.
It's exactly what you need.

426
00:53:36,172 --> 00:53:37,298
Okay.

427
00:53:46,682 --> 00:53:48,893
<i>Like a virgin</i>

428
00:53:50,311 --> 00:53:52,980
<i>Touched for the very first time</i>

429
00:53:53,731 --> 00:53:56,818
<i>Like a virgin</i>

430
00:53:58,402 --> 00:54:00,738
- Okay, who is it?
- I don't know.

431
00:54:02,365 --> 00:54:03,491
Okay.

432
00:54:11,499 --> 00:54:15,753
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

433
00:54:16,212 --> 00:54:21,175
<i>Happy birthday, Mr. President</i>

434
00:54:21,509 --> 00:54:22,969
I don't know.

435
00:54:32,687 --> 00:54:34,021
Moustache.

436
00:54:37,233 --> 00:54:38,276
No.

437
00:54:38,359 --> 00:54:41,863
<i>I'm singing in the rain</i>

438
00:54:41,946 --> 00:54:44,824
<i>Just singing in the rain</i>

439
00:54:44,907 --> 00:54:46,450
<i>What a...</i>

440
00:54:46,534 --> 00:54:47,535
Gene Kelly?

441
00:54:49,203 --> 00:54:52,039
Good. Your turn now.

442
00:54:59,130 --> 00:55:00,631
Okay, pilgrim.

443
00:55:04,552 --> 00:55:06,053
Clint Eastwood?

444
00:55:12,727 --> 00:55:16,564
- I don't know. I give up.
- John Wayne.

445
00:55:18,232 --> 00:55:21,652
I was just about to say that.
I swear. It's amazing.

446
00:55:21,736 --> 00:55:23,696
Leon, really brilliant.

447
00:55:26,532 --> 00:55:27,742
Amazing.

448
00:55:43,299 --> 00:55:46,761
- You love your plant, don't you?
- It's my best friend.

449
00:55:48,012 --> 00:55:50,514
Always happy. No questions.

450
00:55:53,017 --> 00:55:54,894
It's like me, you see.

451
00:55:56,437 --> 00:55:57,730
No roots.

452
00:55:58,397 --> 00:56:01,025
If you really love it, you should
plant it in the middle of a park,

453
00:56:01,108 --> 00:56:03,152
so that it can have roots.

454
00:56:05,112 --> 00:56:06,238
Yeah.

455
00:56:06,322 --> 00:56:10,034
I'm the one you should be watering
if you want me to grow.

456
00:56:11,452 --> 00:56:12,912
You're right.

457
00:56:19,043 --> 00:56:22,505
- No! No!
- Yes! Yes! Yes!

458
00:56:23,756 --> 00:56:25,174
Wait! Stop!

459
00:56:34,433 --> 00:56:37,186
Stop. Stop!

460
00:56:40,189 --> 00:56:44,026
They gotta be jumping out of the plate.
They gotta be alive.

461
00:56:52,994 --> 00:56:55,162
It's been a long time, Leon.

462
00:57:01,377 --> 00:57:02,920
I missed you.

463
00:57:03,629 --> 00:57:07,383
- And you missed some nice jobs, too.
- Been training.

464
00:57:07,883 --> 00:57:11,846
Training's good, but don't overdo it.

465
00:57:12,138 --> 00:57:15,016
You know, training don't pay
as good as working, Leon.

466
00:57:15,099 --> 00:57:16,225
Tony.

467
00:57:19,186 --> 00:57:23,566
All the money I make, that you keep for me...

468
00:57:24,191 --> 00:57:26,944
- You need some money?
- No. Just curious.

469
00:57:27,445 --> 00:57:32,324
Because I've been working a long time
and I haven't done anything with my money.

470
00:57:35,244 --> 00:57:40,291
I thought maybe someday I could use it.

471
00:57:42,293 --> 00:57:43,919
You met a woman.

472
00:57:49,383 --> 00:57:50,509
Leon.

473
00:57:53,054 --> 00:57:55,723
Leon, you got to be careful with women.

474
00:57:55,806 --> 00:57:58,142
Remember when you arrived
in this country, Leon?

475
00:57:58,225 --> 00:58:02,271
When I took you in, you were still
wet behind the fucking ears,

476
00:58:02,730 --> 00:58:05,691
and already you were in deep shit
because of a woman.

477
00:58:05,775 --> 00:58:09,111
- Don't forget that, Leon.
- I wish I could sometimes.

478
00:58:13,157 --> 00:58:15,242
You know, about my money,

479
00:58:15,993 --> 00:58:18,996
maybe I could give

480
00:58:20,164 --> 00:58:21,457
a little

481
00:58:23,667 --> 00:58:25,044
to someone.

482
00:58:26,045 --> 00:58:28,672
You know, to help out.

483
00:58:29,965 --> 00:58:35,513
Hey, it's your money. I mean, I'm just
holding it for you, you know, like a bank.

484
00:58:35,596 --> 00:58:37,765
Except, you know, better than a bank,

485
00:58:37,848 --> 00:58:40,059
because, you know,
banks always get knocked off.

486
00:58:40,142 --> 00:58:42,478
You know, no one knocks off old Tony.

487
00:58:42,561 --> 00:58:44,605
And besides, with a bank,

488
00:58:45,272 --> 00:58:48,609
there's always tons of forms to be filled
and all that shit.

489
00:58:48,692 --> 00:58:53,781
But old Tony, nothing to read,
nothing to write. It's all in his head.

490
00:58:54,782 --> 00:58:56,742
I know how to read now.

491
00:58:58,953 --> 00:59:02,623
That's good, Leon. Good.

492
00:59:04,792 --> 00:59:09,547
Your money's here. Whenever you want it,
you just ask me. Okay?

493
00:59:09,630 --> 00:59:12,091
- Here's a grand. No, no. Come on.
- It's okay. I don't need it.

494
00:59:12,174 --> 00:59:13,968
- Come on. Take it. Have some fun.
- No.

495
00:59:14,051 --> 00:59:16,387
- Go ahead. Take it.
