01:57:28,417 --> 01:57:29,668
You okay?

998
01:57:29,835 --> 01:57:33,964
Hey, I need a medic over here!
Move your fucking asses.

999
01:57:34,340 --> 01:57:36,717
Squad Number One,
what's the status on the apartment?

1000
01:57:36,800 --> 01:57:39,511
<i>Can't see shit. Too much smoke in here.
Give us five minutes to clear it out.</i>

1001
01:57:39,595 --> 01:57:40,554
Okay. You got it.

1002
01:57:40,637 --> 01:57:44,433
What, what, what? You're 200 men
and you can't find one man and a girl?

1003
01:57:44,516 --> 01:57:45,851
Did you find the girl?

1004
01:57:55,611 --> 01:57:58,781
Hi, how are you doing?
Take your mask off, quick.

1005
01:58:00,908 --> 01:58:04,661
Let me see you. That's deep. Right.
And this one here...

1006
01:58:05,037 --> 01:58:07,915
- You're from the 3rd Precinct?
- Yeah.

1007
01:58:10,709 --> 01:58:13,921
All right, let's open up his sleeve a little bit.

1008
01:58:16,924 --> 01:58:19,968
All right, fine. Put it down. Put it down.
This one.

1009
01:58:37,027 --> 01:58:39,071
You stay there for two minutes.
I'll be right back.

1010
01:58:39,154 --> 01:58:42,574
Let me put the mask back on.
I breathe better with it.

1011
01:58:43,242 --> 01:58:45,702
Okay. You're all right. Sit tight.

1012
01:58:52,584 --> 01:58:54,586
Okay, come on, everybody out!

1013
01:58:54,795 --> 01:58:58,090
Come on, let's go, let's go, let's go!
Come on. Out!

1014
01:59:22,322 --> 01:59:24,741
Clear the way. Clear the way, men.

1015
01:59:34,376 --> 01:59:36,879
Come on. What are you doing here?
Get out. Get out. Come on.

1016
02:01:28,699 --> 02:01:30,033
Stansfield.

1017
02:01:30,993 --> 02:01:32,578
At your service.

1018
02:01:41,545 --> 02:01:44,673
This is from

1019
02:01:51,263 --> 02:01:52,556
Mathilda.

1020
02:02:09,573 --> 02:02:10,574
Shit.

1021
02:02:32,262 --> 02:02:33,305
Get out of here!

1022
02:02:37,267 --> 02:02:40,937
Leon asked me to help you out
if something happened,

1023
02:02:42,314 --> 02:02:44,816
and I think something happened, right?

1024
02:02:44,900 --> 02:02:47,402
He put aside a little cash for you.

1025
02:02:47,569 --> 02:02:52,449
So what I'm suggesting is that
seeing as how you're still so young,

1026
02:02:53,325 --> 02:02:56,328
I should hold the money for you
until you're older.

1027
02:02:56,453 --> 02:02:57,412
Like a bank, you know,

1028
02:02:57,496 --> 02:03:02,292
except it's better than a bank, 'cause,
you know, banks always get knocked off.

1029
02:03:02,793 --> 02:03:06,046
No one knocks off old Tony.
But it's your money.

1030
02:03:06,672 --> 02:03:11,176
In the meantime,
all you gotta do is come here

1031
02:03:11,259 --> 02:03:15,889
every once in a while and I'll dish it out
so you can have a little fun, okay?

1032
02:03:18,308 --> 02:03:19,393
Here.

1033
02:03:19,893 --> 02:03:24,022
- Here's a hundred bucks to start with.
- Can't I get a job instead?

1034
02:03:24,481 --> 02:03:25,649
A job?

1035
02:03:28,026 --> 02:03:30,779
- What the hell can you do?
- I can clean.

1036
02:03:32,322 --> 02:03:37,244
I ain't got no work for a 12-year-old kid,
so get it out of your goddamn head!

1037
02:03:37,327 --> 02:03:40,872
It's over! The game's over! Leon's dead!

1038
02:03:42,290 --> 02:03:43,667
You hear me?

1039
02:03:54,010 --> 02:03:56,722
Come on. You think I ain't hurting, too?

1040
02:04:02,102 --> 02:04:03,603
But he's dead.

1041
02:04:04,688 --> 02:04:09,401
You're gonna forget all this craziness
and get your little ass back to school.

1042
02:04:09,943 --> 02:04:12,904
Now take this money
and get the hell out of here.

1043
02:04:12,988 --> 02:04:15,073
And don't let me see your face
till next month,

1044
02:04:15,157 --> 02:04:19,202
'cause something tells me
I'm about to lose my famous kind streak.

1045
02:05:10,921 --> 02:05:12,255
My parents

1046
02:05:14,758 --> 02:05:18,512
died in a car accident four weeks ago.

1047
02:05:21,348 --> 02:05:22,933
It was terrible.

1048
02:05:25,602 --> 02:05:28,522
You know, we didn't have the time
to get to know one another

1049
02:05:28,605 --> 02:05:30,649
when you first came here,

1050
02:05:30,732 --> 02:05:34,277
but I want you to know that I'm not
the kind of woman who'd let down a child,

1051
02:05:34,361 --> 02:05:37,364
whatever her situation,
whatever her mistake.

1052
02:05:37,447 --> 02:05:42,202
So I'm going to help you and do my best
to welcome you here again.

1053
02:05:44,579 --> 02:05:46,331
But on one condition.

1054
02:05:46,957 --> 02:05:49,626
You have to stop lying to me, Mathilda.

1055
02:05:50,669 --> 02:05:54,047
I want you to take a chance and trust me.

1056
02:05:55,382 --> 02:05:57,801
Now, tell me what happened to you.

1057
02:05:59,052 --> 02:06:00,053
Okay.

1058
02:06:01,888 --> 02:06:06,309
My family got shot down by DEA officers
because of a drug problem.

1059
02:06:08,520 --> 02:06:10,897
I lived with the greatest guy on Earth.

1060
02:06:10,981 --> 02:06:15,652
He was a hit man, the best in town,
but he died this morning.

1061
02:06:15,986 --> 02:06:19,155
And if you don't help me,
I'll be dead by tonight.

1062
02:06:39,509 --> 02:06:42,762
- You know her?
- No. I've never seen her.

1063
02:07:09,497 --> 02:07:11,875
I think we'll be okay here, Leon.
